    {"question": "What is luminosity in the context of particle accelerators?", "ground_truth": "Luminosity measures the beam intensity and interaction rate in a particle collider. Instantaneous luminosity (cm⁻²s⁻¹) determines how many collisions occur per second, while integrated luminosity (fb⁻¹ or pb⁻¹) measures the total data collected. Higher luminosity produces more collision events for analysis."},
