    {"question": "What is dark matter and how does CERN search for it?", "ground_truth": "Dark matter is non-luminous matter constituting ~27% of the universe. CERN experiments search for it via missing transverse energy signatures at ATLAS/CMS, monojet and mono-photon production, and long-lived particle searches, though no conclusive discovery has been made."},
