    {"question": "What is supersymmetry (SUSY) and has it been found at the LHC?", "ground_truth": "Supersymmetry is a theoretical extension of the Standard Model proposing a symmetry between bosons and fermions, with each particle having a superpartner. Despite extensive searches at ATLAS and CMS, no SUSY particles have been discovered, setting strong limits on sparticle masses above ~1-2 TeV."},
